HEADWORD: Tilt hammer
<hw>Tilt" ham`mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A tilted hammer; a heavy
hammer, used in iron works, which is lifted or tilted by projections or
wipers on a revolving shaft; a trip hammer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tilting</ent>⟦br⟧
